type":"text","text":"园来自comet（n.彗星）"},{"type":"entry","text":"nonflammable","headword":"nonflammable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不易燃的(not flammable)"},{"type":"text","text":"[na:n'flaemabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：non（不）+flammable（易燃的）→不易燃的：注意不要和inflammable"},{"type":"text","text":"（adj.易燃的）相混"},{"type":"entry","text":"briny","headword":"briny"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 盐水的，成的(of, relating to, or resembling brine or the sea; salty)"},{"type":"text","text":"['braxni]"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自brine（n.盐水）"},{"type":"entry","text":"geomagnetic","headword":"geomagnetic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 地磁的(of or relating to terrestrial magnetism)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dzi:aumaeg'netrk]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：geo（大地）+magnetic(磁性的）→地磁的"},{"type":"entry","text":"foreknowledge","headword":"foreknowledge"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 预知，先见之明(knowledge of sth. before it happens or exists)"},{"type":"text","text":"[fo:r'na:lrd3]"},{"type":"text","text":"国组合词：fore(预先）+knowledge(知道）→预知"},{"type":"entry","text":"repetition","headword":"repetition"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 重复(the act or an instance of repeating or being repeated); 背诵(recital)"},{"type":"text","text":"[repa'ti{n]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自repeat（v重复）"},{"type":"entry","text":"autograph","headword":"autograph"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.亲笔稿，手迹（something written or made with one's own hand) v.在-上亲"},{"type":"text","text":"[':tagraef]"},{"type":"text","text":"笔签名(to write one’s signature in or on) adj. 亲笔的(being in the writer's own"},{"type":"text","text":"handwriting)"},{"type":"entry","text":"choppy","headword":"choppy"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.波浪起伏的(rough with small waves)：（风）不断改变方向的（changeable;"},{"type":"text","text":"['tfa:pi]"},{"type":"text","text":"variable)"},{"type":"entry","text":"uncommitted","headword":"uncommitted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不受约束的，不承担责任的(not pledged to a particular belief or allegiance)"},{"type":"text","text":"[Anka'mrtrd]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：un（不）+commited（有责任的）→不承担责任的"},{"type":"entry","text":"inefficient","headword":"inefficient"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无效率的(not efficient);无能的，不称职的(incapable; incompetent)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,xnx'fxfnt]"},{"type":"text","text":"an inefficient heating system效率不佳的暖气系统"},{"type":"entry","text":"determinant","headword":"determinant"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.决定因素(sth. that determines or decides how sth.happens) adj.决定性的"},{"type":"text","text":"[dr't3:rminant]"},{"type":"text","text":"(decisive)"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自determine（v决定，下决心）"},{"type":"entry","text":"perpetrate","headword":"perpetrate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 范罪(to commit): 负责(to be responsible for)"},{"type":"text","text":"['p3:rpatrert]"},{"type":"entry","text":"self-adulation","headword":"self-adulation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 自我吹捧(the act of praising or flattering excessively by oneself)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,selfaedza'lerfn]"},{"type":"text","text":"It is ironic that a critic of such overwhelming vanity now suffers from a"},{"type":"text","text":"measure of the oblivion to which he was forever consigning others; in the end, all"},{"type":"text","text":"his seif-adulation has only worked against him."},{"type":"entry","text":"impound","headword":"impound"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 限制(to confine);依法没收，扣押(to seize and hold in the custody of the law;"}]},{"number":346,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 31 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"forested","headword":"forested"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.树木丛生的(wooded)"},{"type":"text","text":"[f:rrstId]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自forest（n.森林）"},{"type":"entry","text":"cautionary","headword":"cautionary"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj劝人谨慎的，警戒的（giving advice ora warning）"},{"type":"text","text":"['ko:{aneri]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：caution（小v心，谨慎）+ary→劝人谨慎的，警戒的"},{"type":"text","text":"admonishing. admonitory, cautioning, monitory"},{"type":"entry","text":"humane","headword":"humane"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.人道的，慈悲的(marked by compassion, sympathy, or consideration for"},{"type":"text","text":"[hju:'mern]"},{"type":"text","text":"humans or animals);人文主义的(humanistic)"},{"type":"text","text":"humane treatment 人道的待遇"},{"type":"entry","text":"artisan","headword":"artisan"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 技工(skilled workman or craftsman)"},{"type":"text","text":"['a:rtazn]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：artis（看作arti，技巧）+an（人）→精通技巧之人→技工"},{"type":"entry","text":"unstable","headword":"unstable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不稳定的(not stable)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'sterbl]"},{"type":"text","text":"国联想记忆：un（不)+stable（稳定的）→不稳定的"},{"type":"entry","text":"untimely","headword":"untimely"},{"type":"definition","text":"adji. 过早的(occurring or done before the due, natural, or proper time); 不合时宜"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'tarmli]"},{"type":"text","text":"的(inopportune, unseasonable)"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：un（不）+timely（及时的，适时的）→不合时宜的"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj勇收的(brave)"},{"type":"entry","text":"valorous","headword":"valorous"},{"type":"text","text":"[valaras]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：val（强大）+or（表名词）+ous表形容词）→勇敢使人强大→勇敢的"},{"type":"entry","text":"piercing","headword":"piercing"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 冷得刺骨的(penetratingly cold);敏锐的(perceptive)"},{"type":"text","text":"('pirsin]"},{"type":"text","text":"shrill"},{"type":"entry","text":"embryological","headword":"embryological"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj胚胎学的"},{"type":"text","text":"[embria'la:d3rkl]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：embryo（发芽）+logical（---学的）→胚胎学的"},{"type":"entry","text":"flaunty","headword":"flaunty"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj炫耀的，虚华的(ostentatious)"},{"type":"text","text":"[fo:nti]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自flaunt（v.炫耀，夸耀）"},{"type":"entry","text":"procurement","headword":"procurement"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.取得，获得(the obtaining by effort or careful attention);采购"},{"type":"text","text":"[pra'kjurmant]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自动词procure（v取得，获得）"},{"type":"text","text":"留 Remelting old metal cans rather than making primary aluminum from bauxite"},{"type":"text","text":"ore shipped from overseas saves producers millions of dollars in procurement"},{"type":"text","text":"and production costs."},{"type":"entry","text":"archetypally","headword":"archetypally"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.典型地"},{"type":"text","text":"[a:rki'tapali]"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自archetype (n.典型)"},{"type":"entry","text":"parasitic","headword":"parasitic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.寄生的"},{"type":"text","text":"[paera'srtrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"B The tapeworm is an example of a parasitic organism, one that lives within or"}]},{"number":347,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"relieved","headword":"relieved"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.宽慰的，如释重负的(experiencing or showing relief especially from anxiety"},{"type":"text","text":"[rr'li:vd]"},{"type":"text","text":"or penit-up emotions)"},{"type":"text","text":"Sponsors of the bill were relievec because there was no opposition to it within"},{"type":"text","text":"the legislature until after the measure had been signed into law."},{"type":"entry","text":"custodian","headword":"custodian"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 管理员，监护人(a person who has the custody or care of sth.; caretaker)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kA'staudian]"},{"type":"entry","text":"untouched","headword":"untouched"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.未触动过的，未改变的（not changed in any way)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'tAtt]"},{"type":"text","text":"uninfliuenced, unswayed"},{"type":"entry","text":"bulky","headword":"bulky"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.庞大的（large of its kind);笨重的(corpulent)"},{"type":"text","text":"['bAlki]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自bulk（n.大体积：大部分）"},{"type":"entry","text":"innocence","headword":"innocence"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 无率，清白(the quality of being innocent)"},{"type":"text","text":"['inasns]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：in（无）+noc（伤害）+ence→无辜，清白"},{"type":"text","text":"Melodramas, which presented stark oppositions between innocence and"},{"type":"text","text":"criminality, virtue and corruption, good and evil, were popular precisely because"},{"type":"text","text":"they offered the audience a world devoid of neutrality."},{"type":"text","text":"hibernate"},{"type":"entry","text":"phobia","headword":"phobia"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 恐惧症(an exaggerated ilogical fear)"},{"type":"text","text":"[faubia]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：phob（恐惧）+ia（表病）→恐惧症"},{"type":"entry","text":"hurl","headword":"hurl"},{"type":"text","text":"用力投挪(to throw with force);大声叫骂(to shout out violently)"},{"type":"text","text":"[hs:rl]"},{"type":"text","text":"fling. yell"},{"type":"entry","text":"conventionalize","headword":"conventionalize"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 使按惯例，使习俗化(to make conventional)"},{"type":"text","text":"[kan'venfanalarz]"},{"type":"text","text":"国联想记忆：convention（习俗）+alize（使）→使习俗化"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 爆发, 进发(a violent expression of feeling: eruption); 激增(a surge of activity"},{"type":"entry","text":"posthumously","headword":"posthumously"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv. 死后地(after death)"},{"type":"text","text":"['pa:stfamasli]"},{"type":"text","text":"Like many other pioneers, Dr. Elizabeth Blackwell, founder of the New York"},{"type":"text","text":"Infirmary, the first American hospital staffed entirely by women, faced ridicule"},{"type":"text","text":"from her conitemporaries but has received great honor posthumously."},{"type":"entry","text":"blameworthy","headword":"blameworthy"}]},{"number":348,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 31 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"illegitimate","headword":"illegitimate"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不合法的(illegal; unlawful); 私生的(born of parents not married)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,rla'dzrtamat]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：il不）+legitimate（合法的）→不合法的"},{"type":"text","text":"An example of an illegitimate method of argument is to lump dissimilar cases"},{"type":"example","text":"together deliberately under the pretense that the same principles apply to each."},{"type":"entry","text":"reigning","headword":"reigning"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj统治的，起支配作用的"},{"type":"text","text":"['rernin]"},{"type":"entry","text":"disenfranchise","headword":"disenfranchise"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 剥夺-的权利to deprive of a franchise, of a legal right, or of some privilege or"},{"type":"text","text":"[,disin'fraentfarz]"},{"type":"text","text":"immunity)"},{"type":"entry","text":"disrupt","headword":"disrupt"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 使混乱(to cause disorder in sth.);使中断(to break apart)"},{"type":"text","text":"[dis'rapt]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：dis（加强）+rupt（断裂）→使断裂开→使中断"},{"type":"entry","text":"circulate","headword":"circulate"},{"type":"text","text":"循环：流通（to move around)：发行（to distribute)"},{"type":"text","text":"['s3:rkjalert]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：circ（圆，环）+ulate→绕圈走→循环"},{"type":"entry","text":"tenet","headword":"tenet"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.信条(a principle, belief, or doctrine generally held to be true);教义"},{"type":"text","text":"['tenrt]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：ten（握住）+et→紧抓不放的东西→信条"},{"type":"text","text":"*The show must go on* is the oldest tener of show business; every true"},{"type":"text","text":"performer lives by that creed."},{"type":"entry","text":"injurious","headword":"injurious"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 有害的(harmful)"},{"type":"text","text":"[n'dsurarias]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自injury（n.伤害）"},{"type":"entry","text":"tussle","headword":"tussle"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.扭打，争斗(a physical contest or struggle)：争辩(an intense argument;"},{"type":"text","text":"['tAsI]"},{"type":"text","text":"controversy) v 扭打，争斗(to struggle roughly)"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：tuss（看作fuss，忙乱）+le→为什么忙乱，因为有人扭打搏斗→扭打，"},{"type":"text","text":"争斗"},{"type":"entry","text":"obtainable","headword":"obtainable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 能得到的(capable of being obtained)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ab'ternabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自obtain（v.得到）"},{"type":"text","text":"attainable, available, procurable, securable"},{"type":"entry","text":"inexcusable","headword":"inexcusable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.不可原谅的，不可宽恕的(impossible to excuse or justify)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,nik'skju:zabl]"},{"type":"entry","text":"factorable","headword":"factorable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.能分解成因子的(capable of being factored)"},{"type":"text","text":"['faektarabl]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：factor（因素）+able（能---的）→能分解成因素→能分解成因子的"},{"type":"entry","text":"ill-prepared","headword":"ill-prepared"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj准备不足的(not ready for sth.)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,rlprr'perd]"},{"type":"text","text":"As former Supreme Court Justice Warren Burger was fond of pointing out,"},{"type":"text","text":"many lawyers are not legal hotshots; they often come to court ill-preparec and"},{"type":"text","text":"lacking professional skills."},{"type":"entry","text":"improvident","headword":"improvident"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.无远见的，不节俭的（lacking foresight or thrift)"},{"type":"text","text":"[m'pra:vidant]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：im（不）+provident（有远见的：节俭的）→无远见的，不节俭的"},{"type":"text","text":"Left to endure a penniless old age, the improvidenf man lived to regret his"},{"type":"text","text":"prodigal youth."}]},{"number":349,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"streak","headword":"streak"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 条纹(a line or mark of a different color or texture from the ground) v 加线条(to"},{"type":"text","text":"[stri:k]"},{"type":"text","text":"have a streak)"},{"type":"text","text":"留 People who don't outgrow their colleges often don't grow in other ways; there"},{"type":"text","text":"remained in Forster’s life and imagination a streak of the undergraduate, clever"},{"type":"text","text":"but immature."},{"type":"entry","text":"orbital","headword":"orbital"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad.轨道的"},{"type":"text","text":"['s:rbrtl]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自orbit（n.轨道v.绕轨道运行）"},{"type":"entry","text":"stained","headword":"stained"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj污染的，玷污的"},{"type":"text","text":"[stexnd]"},{"type":"text","text":"blemished, discolored, marked, spotted, tarnished"},{"type":"entry","text":"inducible","headword":"inducible"},{"type":"definition","text":"adji. 可诱导的(capable of being induced)"},{"type":"text","text":"[n'du:sabl]"},{"type":"entry","text":"habituate","headword":"habituate"},{"type":"text","text":".使习惯于(to make used to; accustom)"},{"type":"text","text":"[ha'brtfuert]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：habit（有：拿）+uate→使习惯于"},{"type":"entry","text":"titular","headword":"titular"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.有名无实的，名义上的(existing in title only)"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自title（n.头衔）"},{"type":"text","text":"['trtfalar]"},{"type":"entry","text":"forlorn","headword":"forlorn"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj孤独的(abandoned or deserted);凄凉的(wretched, miserable)"},{"type":"text","text":"[far'lo:rn]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：for（出去）+lorn（被弃的）→抛弃→孤独的"},{"type":"entry","text":"sun-bronzed","headword":"sun-bronzed"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj被太阳晒成古铜色的"},{"type":"text","text":"['sAnbra:nzd]"},{"type":"entry","text":"indulge","headword":"indulge"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 放纵，纵容(to allow to have whatever one likes or wants); 满足(to satisfy a"},{"type":"text","text":"[In'dAld3]"},{"type":"text","text":"perhaps unwarranted desire)"},{"type":"text","text":"cosset, pamper, spoil"},{"type":"definition","text":"v 解数(to save or set free from harm, danger, or loss); 把"},{"type":"entry","text":"uncommunicative","headword":"uncommunicative"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.不爱说话的，拘谨的(not disposed to talk or impart"},{"type":"text","text":"[Anka'mju:nrkatrv]"},{"type":"text","text":"information)"},{"type":"note","text":"园联想记忆：un（不）+communicative（乐意沟通的）→不爱说话的"},{"type":"entry","text":"discomfited","headword":"discomfited"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 困感的，旭龙尬的(frustrated, embarrassed)"},{"type":"text","text":"[drs'kAmfrtrd]"},{"type":"text","text":"While not completely nonplussed by the unusually caustic responses from"},{"type":"text","text":"members of the audlience, the speaker was nonetheless visibly discomfited by"},{"type":"text","text":"their lively criticism."},{"type":"entry","text":"erratically","headword":"erratically"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv. 不规律地，不定地(in an erratic and unpredictable manner)"},{"type":"text","text":"[r'raetrkli]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自erratic（acdj.无规律的）"},{"type":"entry","text":"interpolate","headword":"interpolate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.插入(to insert between or among others)：(通过插入新语句）慕改(to alter by"},{"type":"text","text":"[rn't3:rpalert]"},{"type":"text","text":"putting in new words)"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：inter（在…-之间）+pol（(打磨，润饰）+ate→插入"}]},{"number":350,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 31 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"atheist","headword":"atheist"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 无神论者(one who believes that there is no deity)"},{"type":"text","text":"[erdirst]"},{"type":"entry","text":"unspotted","headword":"unspotted"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.清白的，无污点的(without spot; flawless)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'spa:tid]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：un（不）+spot（污点）+ted→无污点的"},{"type":"entry","text":"textured","headword":"textured"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad手摸时有感觉的：有织纹的"},{"type":"text","text":"['tekst[ard]"},{"type":"text","text":"圈来自texture（n.质地；结构）"},{"type":"entry","text":"ill-repute","headword":"ill-repute"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.名誉败坏（bad fame)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,xlrr'pju:t]"},{"type":"entry","text":"notoriousness","headword":"notoriousness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.委托(piece of work given to sb. to do);佣金(payment to sb. for selling goods)"},{"type":"entry","text":"commission","headword":"commission"},{"type":"text","text":"[ka'mx{n]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：com（共同）+miss（送，放出）+ion→共同送出→委托"},{"type":"entry","text":"inordinate","headword":"inordinate"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj过度的，过分的(immoderate;excessive)"},{"type":"text","text":"[n's:rdinat]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：in（无）+ordin（命令：秩序）+ate→无序的→过度的，过分的"},{"type":"text","text":"In the absence of native predators to stop their spread, imported deer thrived to"},{"type":"text","text":"such an inorclinafe degree that they overgrazed the countryside and threatened"},{"type":"text","text":"the native vegetation."},{"type":"entry","text":"treatise","headword":"treatise"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 论文(a long written work dealing systematically with one subject)"},{"type":"text","text":"['tri:trs]"},{"type":"note","text":"图联想记忆：treat（对待）+ise→对待问题→论文"},{"type":"entry","text":"submission","headword":"submission"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.从属，服从(an act of submitting to the authority or control of another)"},{"type":"text","text":"[sab'mxfn]"},{"type":"text","text":"围词根记忆：sub（下面）+miss(故）+ion→放在下面→从属，服从"},{"type":"text","text":"The losing animal in a struggle saves itself from destruction by an act of"},{"type":"text","text":"submission, an act usually recognized and accepted by the winner."},{"type":"entry","text":"unconvinced","headword":"unconvinced"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 不信服的(not certain that sth. is true or right)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,Ankan'vinst]"},{"type":"text","text":"B Many of her followers remain loyal to her, and even those who have rejected"},{"type":"text","text":"her leadership are unconvinced of the wisdom of replacing her during the"},{"type":"text","text":"current turmoil."},{"type":"entry","text":"ineptitude","headword":"ineptitude"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 无能; 不适当(the quality or state of being inept)"},{"type":"text","text":"[x'neptrtu:d]"},{"type":"entry","text":"graphic","headword":"graphic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj图表的（of graphs)：生动的(vivid）"},{"type":"text","text":"['graefik]"},{"type":"text","text":"图来自graph（n.图表，图解）"},{"type":"entry","text":"pictorial","headword":"pictorial"},{"type":"entry","text":"salvation","headword":"salvation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 拯数(deliverance from the power and effects of sin); 救助(deliverance from"},{"type":"text","text":"[sael'verfn]"},{"type":"text","text":"danger or difficulty)"},{"type":"entry","text":"burst","headword":"burst"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.爆炸;爆裂(to break open,apart, or into pieces);突然发生(to emerge or"},{"type":"text","text":"[b3irst]"},{"type":"text","text":"spring suddenly)"},{"type":"entry","text":"touched","headword":"touched"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 被感动的(emotionally stirred)"},{"type":"text","text":"[tt/t]"},{"type":"text","text":"affected, inspired, moved"},{"type":"entry","text":"restoration","headword":"restoration"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 恢复，复原(an act of restoring or the condlition of being restored)"},{"type":"text","text":"[resta'rerfn]"},{"type":"text","text":"Despite careful restoration and cleaning of the murals in the 1960s, the colors"},{"type":"text","text":"slowly but steadily deteriorated."},{"type":"entry","text":"dose","headword":"dose"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 剂量，(—)剂(an exact amount of a medicine)"},{"type":"text","text":"[daus]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：dos（给予）+e→给予力量→剂量"}]},{"number":351,"blocks":[{"type":"text","text":"<<<GRE词汇精选乱序版"},{"type":"entry","text":"transitional","headword":"transitional"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 转变的，变迁的(of, relating to, or characterized by transition)"},{"type":"text","text":"[traen'zi[anl]"},{"type":"text","text":"Current data suggest that, although transitiona/ states between fear and"},{"type":"text","text":"aggression exist, fear and aggression are as distinct physiologically as they are"},{"type":"text","text":"psychologically."},{"type":"entry","text":"unleash","headword":"unleash"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.发泄，释放(to set feelings and forces free from control)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'li:]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：un（不）+leash（控制，约束）→不去控制→发泄"},{"type":"entry","text":"clannish","headword":"clannish"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 排他的， 门户之见的(tending to associate closely with one's own group and"},{"type":"text","text":"['klaenx]"},{"type":"text","text":"to avoid others)"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：clan（宗派，家族）+nish→门户之见的"},{"type":"entry","text":"suppliant","headword":"suppliant"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj恩求的，哀求的(humbly imploring)n.恳求者，哀求者（one who supplicates)"},{"type":"text","text":"['sapliant]"},{"type":"text","text":"beggar, prayer, suitor, supplicant"},{"type":"entry","text":"bygone","headword":"bygone"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj过去的（gone by)"},{"type":"text","text":"[bargo:n]"},{"type":"definition","text":"a bygone age过去的年代"},{"type":"entry","text":"allusive","headword":"allusive"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.暗指的，间接提到的(containing allusions)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'lu:s1v]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：al(加强）+lud（戏剧）+sive→不直截了当→陪指的"},{"type":"entry","text":"awe-struck","headword":"awe-struck"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.充满敬畏的（filled with awe）"},{"type":"text","text":"['o:strAk]"},{"type":"text","text":"围组合词：awe（敬畏）+struck（打动）→充满敬畏的"},{"type":"entry","text":"conifer","headword":"conifer"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 针o树(a tree that has leaves like needles)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ka:nrfar]"},{"type":"note","text":"联想记忆：con（看作cone，圆锥，松果）+i+fer（带来）→带来松果的树→针叶树"},{"type":"entry","text":"egocentric","headword":"egocentric"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.利己的(self-centered)"},{"type":"text","text":"[i:gau'sentrrk]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：ego（我）+centr（中心）+ic→以自我为中心的→利己的"},{"type":"entry","text":"scavenge","headword":"scavenge"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.清除（to cleanse)：从废物中提取有用物质（to salvage from discarded or refuse"},{"type":"text","text":"['skaevind3]"},{"type":"text","text":"material)"},{"type":"entry","text":"crossfire","headword":"crossfire"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.交叉火力"},{"type":"text","text":"['kro:sfarar]"},{"type":"text","text":"国组合词：cross交叉）+fire（火）→交叉火力"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.传送，传插（to send or convey from one person or"},{"type":"entry","text":"gloom","headword":"gloom"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.昏暗(darkness;dimness;obscurity)：优郁(deep"},{"type":"text","text":"[glu:m]"},{"type":"text","text":"sadness or hopelessness)"},{"type":"text","text":"Our mood swings about the economy grow more"},{"type":"text","text":"extreme: when things go well, we become euphoric;"},{"type":"text","text":"when things go poorly, gloom descends."},{"type":"entry","text":"soundproof","headword":"soundproof"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 使隔音(to insulate so as to obstruct the passage of sound) adj 隔音的"},{"type":"text","text":"['saundpru:f]"},{"type":"text","text":"soundproof door隔音门"},{"type":"entry","text":"enrage","headword":"enrage"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.激怒，触怒(to make sb. very angry)"},{"type":"text","text":"[xn'reid3]"},{"type":"note","text":"图词根记忆：en（使）+rage（疯狂）→使人疯狂→激怒"},{"type":"entry","text":"distent","headword":"distent"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj 膨胀的(swollen); 扩张的(expanded)"}]},{"number":352,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"Word List 31 >>>"},{"type":"entry","text":"expertise","headword":"expertise"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 专门技术，专业知识(the skill knowledge, judgment of an expert)"},{"type":"text","text":"[eksp3r'ti:z]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自expert（n.专家）"},{"type":"entry","text":"pounce","headword":"pounce"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. (猛禽的)爪(the claw of a bird of prey); 猛扑(the act of pouncing) v 猛扑(to"},{"type":"text","text":"[pauns]"},{"type":"text","text":"swoop upon and seize sth. with or as if with talons);突然袭击(to make a sudiden"},{"type":"text","text":"assault or approach)"},{"type":"text","text":"pounceon突然袭击"},{"type":"entry","text":"titanic","headword":"titanic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj巨人的，力大无比的(colossal)"},{"type":"text","text":"[tar'taenrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"园来自希腊神话中的巨神Titan，也可以联想电影Titanic（《泰坦尼克号》）。"},{"type":"entry","text":"abolition","headword":"abolition"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 度除, 度上(the state of being abolished; prohibition)"},{"type":"text","text":"[aeba'lx{n]"},{"type":"text","text":"圆来自abolish（v腹除，废止）"},{"type":"entry","text":"waxy","headword":"waxy"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 像蜡的，苍白的，光滑的(looking or feeling like wax)"},{"type":"text","text":"[waeksi]"},{"type":"entry","text":"timeliness","headword":"timeliness"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.及时，适时"},{"type":"text","text":"国来自timely （adj及时的，适时的）"},{"type":"text","text":"['taxmlinas]"},{"type":"entry","text":"optimum","headword":"optimum"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj最有利的，最理想的（most favorable or desirable)"},{"type":"text","text":"['a:ptrmam]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：optim（最好的）+um→最有利的"},{"type":"entry","text":"nonconformist","headword":"nonconformist"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj不墨守成规的n.不墨守成规的人"},{"type":"text","text":"[na:nkan'fo:rmist]"},{"type":"text","text":"国词根记忆：non（不）+conform（遵守）+ist→不墨守成规的人"},{"type":"entry","text":"unmitigated","headword":"unmitigated"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.未缓和的，未减轻的(not lessoned or excused in any way)"},{"type":"text","text":"[An'mrtigertrd]"},{"type":"note","text":"园词根记忆：un（不）+mitigate（缓和的）+d→未缓和的"},{"type":"entry","text":"tread","headword":"tread"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.踏，践踏(to press beneath the feet; trample);行走 n.步态；车轮胎面"},{"type":"text","text":"[tred]"},{"type":"text","text":"step"},{"type":"entry","text":"trilogy","headword":"trilogy"},{"type":"definition","text":"n. 三部曲(a group of three related books)"},{"type":"text","text":"['trrlad3i]"},{"type":"note","text":"圆词根记忆：tri（三）+logy（说话，作品）→三部曲"},{"type":"entry","text":"refrigerate","headword":"refrigerate"},{"type":"definition","text":"v. 使冷却, 冷藏(to make or keep cold or cool)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rx'fridsarert]"},{"type":"entry","text":"philosophic","headword":"philosophic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 哲学(家)(of or relating to philosophers or philosophy)"},{"type":"text","text":"[,frla'sa:frk]"},{"type":"text","text":"来自philosophy（n.哲学）"},{"type":"entry","text":"impart","headword":"impart"},{"type":"definition","text":"v传授，赋予（bestow);传递（transmit)：告知，透露（to make known)"},{"type":"text","text":"[rm'pa:rt]"},{"type":"note","text":"词根记忆：im（进入）+part（部分）→（引导人）进入（知识的）一部分以让他知道→"},{"type":"text","text":"告知"},{"type":"entry","text":"operable","headword":"operable"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj.可操作的，可使用的（fit,possible,or desirable to use)：可手术治疗的（that"},{"type":"text","text":"['a:parabl]"},{"type":"text","text":"can be treated by an operation)"},{"type":"entry","text":"acoustic","headword":"acoustic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 听觉的，声音的(having to do with hearing or sound)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'ku:strk]"},{"type":"text","text":"最后三天"}]},{"number":353,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"personally","headword":"personally"},{"type":"definition","text":"adv.亲自(in person);作为个人（as a person)"},{"type":"text","text":"['ps:rsanali]"},{"type":"text","text":"Despite the daunting size of her undergraduate class, the professor made"},{"type":"definition","text":"a point of getting to know as many as possible of the more than 700 students"},{"type":"text","text":"personally."},{"type":"entry","text":"interrogation","headword":"interrogation"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.审问，质问；疑问句"},{"type":"text","text":"[rn,tera'ger{n]"},{"type":"text","text":"inquiry, query, question"},{"type":"entry","text":"sarcastic","headword":"sarcastic"},{"type":"definition","text":"adj. 讽刺的(sneering, caustic, ironic)"},{"type":"text","text":"[sa:r'kaestrk]"},{"type":"text","text":"sarcasticcomments讽刺的评论"},{"type":"entry","text":"apportion","headword":"apportion"},{"type":"definition","text":"v.(按比例或计划)分配(to divide and share out according to a plan)"},{"type":"text","text":"[a'po:rfn]"},{"type":"text","text":"图apportion sth.among/between/to sb.分配，分发"}]}]}